<div class="subheading">
<sub_heading>
<h1>Eligible Witnesses to a Mortgage Document</h1>
</sub_heading>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">
<p style="text-align: right;"><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/processes/new-applications/new-application-process.aspx" target="_blank">Back to Paperless Application Process</a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Security Documents witnessed in Australia and Overseas must be witnessed in accordance with the requirements of each state. Refer to the following table for details.</p>
<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th>State or territory</th>
<th>Within Australia</th>
<th>Outside Australia</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ACT</td>
<td><p>N/A - Witnessing not required</p> </td>
<td><p>N/A - witnessing  not required</p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>NSW</td>
<td><p>Any adult (that is, over age 18) who:</p>
<ul>
<li>is not a party to the transaction; and</li>
<li>has personally known the mortgagor for at least 12 months or sighted copies of identification documents confirming their identity.</li>
</ul> <p>Refer to the NSW Land and Property Information website <a href="http://rgdirections.lpi.nsw.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0007/163348/Witness_obligations.pdf" target="_blank">fact sheet</a>, for a list of acceptable identification documents.</p> </td>
<td><p>Any adult (that is, over age 18) who:</p>
<ul>
<li>is not a party to the transaction; and</li>
<li>has personally known the mortgagor for at least 12 months or sighted copies of identification documents confirming their identity. </li>
</ul> <p>Refer to the NSW Land and Property Information website, for a list of acceptable identification documents.</p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>TAS/VIC</td>
<td>Any adult (that is, over age 18) who isn't a party to the loan.</td>
<td>Any adult (that is, over age 18) who isn't a party to the loan.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>QLD</td>
<td>A person holding any of the following offices or occupations:
    <ul>
<li>A notary public.</li>
<li>A Justice of the Peace.</li>
<li>A Commissioner for Declarations.</li>
<li>A Lawyer as defined under the Legal Profession Act 2007.</li>
<li>A licenced Conveyancer from another State.</li>
</ul> <p>The <a adhocenable="false" href="https://www.commbroker.com.au/content/dam/commbroker/private/processes/new-applications/qld-witness-doc.pdf" target="_blank">Queensalnd Witnessing information sheet</a> must be issued with the document Pack</p> <p> </p> </td>
<td><p>A person who isn't a party to the document who is one of the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>An Australian Consular Officer or authorised employee of an Australian Embassy, High Commission or Consulate (Australian Consular Office).</li>
<li>A competent officer as defined under the Defence Force Regulation 1952.</li>
<li>A notary public</li>
<li>An Australian Legal Practitioner</li>
<li>An Australian Lawyer</li>
<li>A New Zealand Lawyer (i.e. a solicitor, barrister or barrister and solicitor).</li>
</ul> <p>The witness must also;</p>
<ul>
<li>Identify the mortgagor/s against specific documentation,</li>
<li>Retain copies of the identification documents and</li>
<li>Complete the appropriate “Identity/Witnessing Certification” document.</li>
<li>Refer to <a adhocenable="false" href="https://www.commbroker.com.au/content/dam/commbroker/private/commbroker-forms/qld-witness-doc21%20(2).pdf" target="_blank">Queensland Overseas Witnessing Requirements (006-002)</a>. This form must be issued with the doc pack and the appropriate “Identity/Witnessing Certification” together with certified copies of the documents used to identify the customer must be returned with the executed Mortgage.</li>
</ul> <p> </p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>SA </td>
<td>N/A - witnessing not required</td>
<td>N/A - witnessing not required</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>WA</td>
<td>Any adult (that is, over age 18) who isn't a party to the loan.</td>
<td><p>A person who isn't a party to the loan, and who is Australian consular officer.</p> <p>An Australian consular officer is defined by section 145(4) of the <i>Transfer of Land Act 1893 </i>as a person appointed to hold or act in any of the following offices (being an office of the Commonwealth) in a country or place outside the Commonwealth, such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>ambassador;</li>
<li>minister;</li>
<li>high commissioner;</li>
<li>head of mission;</li>
<li>commissioner;</li>
<li>chargé d'affaires;</li>
<li>consul or secretary at an embassy;</li>
<li>high commissioner's office;</li>
<li>legation or other post;</li>
<li>consular-general;</li>
<li>consul;</li>
<li>vice-consul;</li>
<li>trade commissioner; and</li>
<li>consular agent. </li>
</ul> <p>Additional requirement for transfers:</p> <p>Where a transfer is signed overseas by a transferor, a statutory declaration is to be provided by the conveyancer acting for the transferor which:</p>
<ul>
<li>describes the circumstances of the identity check (i.e. which must comply with Landgate's 100 points requirement); and</li>
<li>has copies of documents used for identification purposes annexed.</li>
</ul> <p>The statutory declaration and supporting information must be provided to Landgate with the transfer being lodged for the registration otherwise it will be requisitioned.</p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>NT</td>
<td><p>A person who isn't party to the loan and who holds any of the following offices or occupations:</p> <p><b>Within the Northern Territory</b></p>
<ul>
<li>A Commissioner for Oaths*</li>
<li>A member of the Legislative Assembly</li>
<li>A Legal Practitioner</li>
<li>A person holding office under the <i>Supreme Court Act</i>, the <i>Justices Act</i>, the <i>Local Court Act</i>  or the <i>Registration Act</i></li>
<li>A member of the Police Force</li>
<li>A person licensed as a Conveyancing agent or real estate agent under the <i>Agents Licensing Act</i></li>
<li>A notary public</li>
<li>Accountant</li>
<li>Branch or Lending Manager of a bank, building society, credit union or the Territory Insurance Office<br/> </li>
<li>CEO of a local government council constituted under the <i>Local Government Act</i></li>
<li>Headmaster or Principal of a Northern Territory school</li>
<li>Justice of the Peace*</li>
<li>Licensed surveyor under the <i>Licensed Surveyors Act</i></li>
<li>Medical Practitioner</li>
<li>Pharmacist</li>
<li>Postmaster or Manager of a post office</li>
</ul> <p>*Note - Commisioner of Oaths and Justice of the Peace must provide their unique registration number when witnessing documents</p> <p><b>Within the rest of Australia</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Accountant</li>
<li>Branch or Lending Manager of a bank, building society or credit union<br/> </li>
<li>Commissioner for Declarations</li>
<li>Commissioner for Oaths</li>
<li>Commissioner for taking Affidavits</li>
<li>Deputy Registrar of Titles</li>
<li>Deputy Registrar-General</li>
<li>Headmaster or Principal of a school</li>
<li>Justice of the Peace</li>
<li>Legal Practitioner</li>
<li>Licensed Conveyancing Agent</li>
<li>Licensed Real Estate Agent</li>
<li>Licensed Surveyor</li>
<li>Medical Practitioner</li>
<li>Member or Officer of a Police Force</li>
<li>Notary Public</li>
<li>Pharmacist</li>
<li>Postmaster or Manager of a post office</li>
<li>Recorder of Titles</li>
<li>Registrar of Titles</li>
<li>Registrar-General</li>
<li>Town clerk or CEO of a local government council</li>
</ul> </td>
<td><p><b>*Outside Australia and the place is a member of the Commonwealth of Nations:</b></p> <p>A person who:</p>
<ul>
<li>isn't a party to the loan;</li>
<li>An Australian Consular Officer or Australian Diplomatic Officer</li>
<li>A person who has authority to take an oath or declaration and whose authority to do so is verified by one of the following:
      <ul>
<li>an officer or judge of the Superior Court of that place;</li>
<li>a British diplomat or a consular agent in the place of execution; </li>
<li>a consular official in the place of execution.</li>
</ul> </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>British diplomat or a consular agent in the place of execution</li>
<li>Notary Public</li>
</ul> <p><b>Any other place outside Australia</b></p>
<ul>
<li>British diplomat or a consular agent in the place of execution</li>
<li>Consular official in the place of execution</li>
<li>Notary Public</li>
</ul> </td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;">Blue or Black ink must be used on the mortgage document. Liquid paper, pencil or red ink must <b>not</b> be used.</li>
<li>Where the witness is a CBA staff member, the address must begin with the wording 'Commonwealth Bank', when the address includes the words 'Shop' or 'Westfield', eg. 'Commonwealth Bank, Shop 123 Westfield Shoppingtown'.</li>
<li>Where the witness is a non CBA staff member, the address must begin with the name of the business when the address includes the words 'Shop' or 'Westfield', eg. 'General Pets Westfield, Shop 123, 100 Smith St Sydney NSW 2000'.</li>
<li>Mortgagor and borrower signatures must be consistent with their names.</li>
<li>Where signing of the Consumer Credit Contract Schedule takes place in office, the borrower's attention must be drawn to Part F (Fees and Charges section) of the Usual Terms and Conditions.</li>
</ul>
